The Pension Transitional Arrangement Directorate (PTAD) has suspended walk-in verification of pensioners under Defined Benefit Scheme (DBS) at its headquarters and state liaison offices from December 15 to January 19, 2021. This was contained in a statement issued by the Head, Corporate Communications, Mr. Gbenga Ajayi, in Abuja on Thursday. READ ALSO: Stealing Retirement Ajayi said the suspension affect the Civil Service Pension Department (CSPD), Police Pensions Department (PPD), Customs, Immigration, Prisons Pension Department (CIPPD) and Parastatal Pension Department (PaPD). READ ALSO: I’ve No Case To Answer On Allegations Against Me, Maina Tells Court Ajayi said that pensioners that had requested for the walk-in verification would be contacted and scheduled for the exercise. He also said pensioners with urgent complaints should report through the directorate’s e-mail. (NAN)